Disappointed with this "Viral" sunscreen 🤯

The @aqualogica.in Glow+ Infused Water Sunscreen was highly marketed by the brand as a "Dupe for the ISDIN" sunscreen, calling it a cheaper and Made in India alternative to the cult favourite 🙈 

But sadly the packaging was faulty, I don't know if it was just the bottle that I received or if anyone else also had the same issue. The cap just kept turning without locking the bottle shut. So I now have to store the sunscreen in an upright position to keep it from spilling 🥲

It also burned the skin around my mouth. I thought I would have to wash it off but the tingling and burning subsided after about 5 minutes. The biggest deal beaker for me was that after blending the sunscreen it turned into an oily sort of texture that just sat on top of my skin. It also made me sweat which is also unpleasant.

Overall, this sunscreen failed on all fronts for me personally 🙈

I've seen a lot of reviews of people praising this sunscreen and loving it. Have you tried this yet? If yes, I'm curious to know your experience. Do let me know in the comments below 💬 

* I haven't tried the @isdin sunscreen yet 

#aqualogica #isdin #sunscreen #spffail #fail #aqualogicasunscreen #viral #spf #dupe

I recently tried the new @dotandkey.skincare Mango Detan Gel Sunscreen and like their other sunscreens, this is another great one! 

It has SPF 50+ & PA++++ which is the highest level of sun protection 😎 

It has a lightweight oil-free gel texture that gets absorbed quickly and leaves a skin like finish. It is even more lightweight than their other sunscreens which is what amazes me. It contains Niacinamide and Alpha Arbutin which help fade tan and hyperpigmentation. 

It is perfect for the current hot and humid weather and will suit all skin types especially oily and combination skin. 

It is available on all major online platforms as well as Dot & Key's official website. You can use my code MEERAB10 for an additional discount 🧡
